jobtitle: Data Analyst (Customer Behaviour) 2 week project - User Journey Mapping
content: Data Analyst (Customer Behaviour) 2 week project - User Journey Mapping Must have: - ABN - Australian Citizen The Opportunity: Your position is vital role within the Crikey Team at Private Media, reporting to the associate publisher where your objective is to map user journeys over the lifecycle of a paid subscriber using historical data provided. The Crikey business model rests almost entirely on subscription revenue, therefore understanding the path to conversion and reasons for user churn is crucial. While we have a clear idea around insights we are hoping to discover, such as identifying content that is most likely to lead to paid subscribers or behaviours most likely to indicate churn, the right candidate will also look for unexpected, useful insights in the data that paint a richer understanding of our users. Responsibilities: • Source and prototype datasets from available audience segmentation and historical user data to map user journeys, and to inform your analysis. • Customer journey analysis, conversion rate optimisation, data analytics and implementation, data visualisation, running experiments to help inform the user conversion process and deliver customer experience and growth. • Analysis and synthesis of customer journey data to build three (3) detailed scenarios around user journey churn and conversion. (Examples include, behaviour that indicates a likelihood to churn at any point in a user life time, the type of content a user begins their Crikey journey on that indicates likelihood to convert to a paid subscriber, the average time taken for users to convert to paid subscribers and the optimal time to market to users based on this.) • Collaborate with the Crikey associate publisher and Private Media’s Digital lead to integrate and validate user journey metrics through Pardot, Parsely and Wordpress in order to provide the foundations for the user journey dashboard. • Write complex queries in SQL and write scripts to draw out useful business insights around user journeys. So what are we looking for? • Initiative, ownership and accountability for what you say you can and will do • Extensive experience with buyer behaviour and segmentation practices including customer journey mapping and audience personas. • Curiosity and a passion for analysing and using data to determine trends and patterns. • You should enjoy enabling successful commercial outcomes and supporting management to make informed decisions. • 2 years of quantitative and qualitative analyst experience (commercial or academic) • Bachelor degree or higher from a discipline that uses advanced statistical modelling (e.g., Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Econometrics, Marketing, Psychology, etc.). • Experience in data extraction - programming experience in SQL and a corresponding understanding of database schemas, data marts and warehouses, and be a great problem solver. • Experience with Digital Analytics tools like Adobe Analytics or Google Analytics, Parsley and Pardot. • Excellent communication skills and an affinity with data modelling, analysis, and reporting. About Us - Crikey: Crikey has been Australia’s leading independent digital news and commentary publication for almost twenty years. We push the boundaries and dig deeper to find the truth. We bring our readers the inside word on what’s really going on in politics, government, media, business, the arts, sports and other aspects of public life in Australia. We reveal how the powerful operate behind the scenes, and tackle the stories insiders are talking about, but other media can’t or won’t cover. Crikey members pay for our journalism because it takes them beyond the mainstream media, beyond the clickbait and beyond the predictability of much modern journalism. Their support allows us to maintain our fierce independence. Our Culture: We really value our culture and the way we work together to get stuff done. We are a group of hard-working, fun and caring people who will support you to have a successful and fulfilling experience with our Crikey team. We have a lean business model to offer a growing portfolio of services to a large number of readers. We offer a collaborative and fun place to work - fast-paced and outcomes focused. We are focused on continuous improvement and still have lots of room for growth and innovation. less

jobtitle: Power BI Power Query Project
content: Overview The data in this project is from a building automation system and the data is in the form of control point trend logs. The data is from a SQL database with each table representing a control panel within a building. The project is to merge the tables into one table such that all merged fields share a common timestamp. Understanding the Source Data The attached PBIX file has the following tables (A) Several dozen “DataTables” (e.g. "2000MTL12") with approx. 8 fields each: ID, Timestamp, TimeChange, Mnemonic1, Mnemonic2, ..., Mnemonic6 (where “Mnemonic” is the name given for the table field names). Note that “DataTable” and “Mnemonic” are the names given to these objects in the reference table BACnet_Config. (B) BACnet_DOPR, which is a table that acts as a cross-reference between the Mnemonic name and what the table calls the “ObjectName” as well as “units”. (c) BACnet_Config, which is a table that cross-reference the Mnemonics with the DataTables they are found in. I don’t think this table is required as the Mnemonics are unique and the originating DataTable names are not needed in the WH. I mentioned the table just in case I am wrong and you need it for the query (D) A number of other tables that aren't important The Project** (1) Merge all the “DataTable” tables into a single new table where each “Mnemonic” shares a common Timestamp (which changes in 30-minute increments). - Where the Timestamp is out by a few seconds between “DataTable” tables make the seconds equal to zero to ensure that the timestamps between tables match perfectly for date and time. - Where the field called TimeChange provides a value delete this row from the tables as this is an error in the data source that supplies Timestamps that do not match the Timestamp records. (2) Replace all the “Mnemonic” field names in the new merged table with the “ObjectName”s in the BACnet_DOPR table. The Mnemonic names are unique and there is a one-to-one relationship in the BACnet_DOPR table between Mnemonic and ObjectName. ** See Excel file for example less

jobtitle: Qualitative survey analysis and write-up needed
content: Hi there, I am looking for someone to do some qualitative analysis of responses to open-ended survey questions, and to write up a short summary of the findings. This project is for one survey, but there will be a subsequent separate project to analyse six further surveys - one per week from 22nd July to 2nd September. I'd ideally like this second project to be undertaken by the same person as this first project, if is a success. Some additional detail: - Survey topic: I work for a UK-based charity called Think Ahead. We run a programme that recruits and trains people to become mental health social workers. The programme runs for two years, and this survey was sent to our programme participants at the end of the two years, asking them about their experience of the programme as a whole . - Number of respondents and questions: There were 40 respondents to the survey, and each answered seven open-ended questions. Most of their answers are 1-3 sentences long. - Type of analysis: I am looking for someone to carry out a thematic analysis - coding responses to each question into themes, and providing a written description of each theme, including some illustrative quotes and a sense of how common/widespread/representative each theme is. Although the analysis needs to be high quality, our ultimate goal is to clearly and accurately understand what our participants are telling us, rather than scientific perfection in and of itself. Output: A short write-up of the themes under each question (e.g. in Microsoft Word), as described above. If it is possible to share details of the analysis too, that would be ideal (e.g. in Excel or an NVivo export) - but it's not a problem if this isn't possible. - Timelines: I am hoping to commission this project asap, so that it can be finished before starting the next project on 22nd July. (Apologies for the short notice - a colleague who was due to carry out this work has had to take time off very suddenly). less

jobtitle: Looking for a Processing Analyst
content: We are a large and growing New York-based e-commerce company, seeking a new addition to our team. Our new Processing Analyst will report directly to our Processing Team Manager. Are you a career minded, energetic and motivated Processing Analyst with a minimum of 2 years experience? Do you enjoy working with cross-cultural teams from all across the globe in a fully remote environment? Please read on! In this role, you will be working alongside the other analysts on various processing related activities. jobtitle: automate strategy for thinkorswim
content: We want to automate this strategy for thinkorswim https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=10VYd7_8E-s&list=PLhKnvfWKsu43lm8AirILMxzwarz4I_bCR How to enter https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fc0Sb8lqX30 Autotrading is a trading plan based around the buying and selling of orders placed automatically from an underlying system or program. The buy or sell orders are sent out to be executed in the market when a certain set of criteria is met. What Is a Bear Call Spread? Bear Call Spread Diagram Source: TheOptionsGuide.com A bear call spread—also known as a credit call spread—is a bearish options strategy that creates a net cash inflow at the onset. By purchasing a long call option and writing a short call option at a lower strike price, the strategy generates an immediate income with a limited gain and loss profile. The limited-risk, limited-reward strategy is ideal in situations where traders are cautiously pessimistic. The strategies key prices to remember include: Maximum Gain – The maximum gain occurs when the stock price falls below both call option strike prices, which results in both options expiring worthless and the initial credit encompassing the profit. Maximum Loss – The maximum loss occurs when the stock price moves above the higher strike price, which results in a loss equal to the difference between the two strike prices minus the net credit received. Breakeven Point – The breakeven point occurs when the stock price is above the lower strike price by the amount of the initial credit received, which would result in the long call expiring worthless and the short evening out. Bear Call Spread Example Suppose that a trader believes that a stock will fall after its earnings announcement, but he or she isn’t confident enough to short the stock outright or use simple put options. By simultaneously buying an SEP 50 call for $100 and selling an SEP 45 call for $300, the trader establishes a bear call spread and receives a net $200 credit for entering the trade – the difference between the two premiums. See also Understanding a Short-Squeeze and How to Profit From One If the stock falls to $44.00 at expiration, as expected following a poor earnings announcement, both options will expire worthless and the trader will keep the entire $200 net credit received at the onset as a profit. If the stock rises to $52.00 instead, both calls expire in the money and the trader will have to buy back the spread for $500, which translates to a $300 loss after the $200 credit. Bear Call Spread Dynamics The bear call spread strategy is ideal in situations where traders are cautiously pessimistic given its limits on profit and loss potential, but there are many different ways to make the strategy profitable in different situations. For example, traders can enter a more aggressive bear call spread by expanding the difference between the two strike prices. These dynamics will increase the initial credit received and thereby the maximum profit potential, although the stock price must move down to a greater degree in order to realize that profit, which introduces more risk on the part of the position as a whole. The Bottom Line The bear call spread strategy is a bearish strategy that’s optimal for traders predicting a moderate decline in price. With its controlled profit and loss profile, traders know exactly how much they can gain or lose on the trade, which sets it apart from riskier strategies like naked puts or short selling. The other key benefit is that the credit is realized upfront and can be reinvested in other trades. less

jobtitle: Data analyst needed familiar with SPSS.
content: Hi, I require data analysis in SPSS for a small clinical trial. The trial was a crossover. The trial was comparing an intervention to placebo for reducing hot flushes (outcomes change in hot flush frequency, severity and average mean score). Other outcomes quality of life scores, pathology tests (liver, renal function, hormone assays), adverse events. Also collected demographics, health history, and Chinese medicine diagnosis, concomitant medication. I require descriptive statistics, including frequency tables and percentages for categorical variables and means, standard deviations and ranges for continuous variables. The sample size was intended to be 84 (allowing for 30% withdrawal rate) however only recruited 14 in the time-frame. Pathology tests and Chinese medicine diagnosis were conducted 3 times. Other data (hot flush data and quality of life, adverse events) was collected at baseline and every 4 weeks (Baseline, Week 1, 5, 9, 13, 17, 21, 25, 29, 33) i.e. 10 times. Trial protocol specified t-tests to compare treatment groups on mean daily hot flush frequency, severity and score and quality of life measures (difference between baseline and last study week of each arm) Chi-squared tests to compare treatment groups on preference data. Cross-over mean daily hot flush frequency, severity and score compared within individuals used paired t-tests among those completing 12 weeks and 28 weeks. Additionally mixed linear analysis to test within-person treatment effect (intervention vs placebo) adjusted for the sequence effect, period effect and the 2 baseline measures to reduce biases (carry over effect). Not sure if these tests will be accurate with such a small sample size. Are there other tests specific for small trials? Additionally, need to analyse the following - Compliance which was monitored with return of intervention sachets that were unused and diary records. Treatment satisfaction collected at the end of each arm. Quality of life was measured at baseline and every 4 weeks with Menopause Specific Quality of Life and Hot Flush Related Daily Interference Scale. As I have never used SPSS before and don't have a mathematical bone in my body I need help to analyse and interpret the data - including writing up results and figures generated in SPSS. Currently the data has been exported from RedCap to Excel. Please advise if interested and what other information you require to quote $. Regards Dianne less

jobtitle: Generic Time Series Modeling with trading data in Python (STATISTICAL MODELING)
content: I am looking for someone to make a time series model to plot an X Y scatter plot based on price data for several assets all at once (several currency pairs would be clustered together and have their own scatter plot, same for commodities, same for cryptocurrency, etc) with "momentum" as the x axis and "mean reverting" as the Y axis. The model would use both the variance ratio test and Ornstein–Uhlenbeck (OU) Process to determine whether if the asset should be classified as a momentum asset or mean reverting asset. I would want the ability to run the model for various the trading periods (i.e. monthly, weekly, daily, 4hr, 1 hr, 30 min, 15 min, 5 min, 1 min). The variance ratio test would plot on the scatter plot based on the following: Decreasing variance/ (variance ratio between 0 and .8), a random walk (.8 to 1.2) or increasing variance/momentum (ratio of 1.2 to 2). The OU process would calculate the mean reversion rate. I would want to visualize whether the mean reversion rate was high or low on the plot and be able to compare that to the results of the variance ratio test. So essentially, I am looking for a scatter plot that plots results for two test (variance ratio test and OU process) using a cluster of trading data (i.e. currency pair data, etc) for different time frames. I am looking for a way to constantly scan the markets (multiple assets) and determine the results of the tests on this scatter plot at any given time. less

jobtitle: Python Data Scientist for Analysis of Relational Database + Friendly Tutoring
content: This contract includes a few sub-projects. For this project you will work on two things: 1) STAGE 1: Quantitative Analysis Conduct a rigorous analysis of a large relational database. All your coding must be done in Python + associated libraries + BigQuery or PostgressQL (or something very similar and easy). After the general quantitative analysis has been finished, you will conduct a machine learning analysis using Tensorflow (Keras API). Once your analysis is complete, you will produce a series visualizations and tables. Deliverables will include jupyter notebooks. This stage will be short and intense and take up to one month. You will mostly work alone. Once this analysis is complete, it will be examined by another data scientist (an experienced in-house consultant) in our location to verify the quality of the analysis. 2) STAGE 2: Stats Tutoring Once you have completed stage 1, you will provide tutorship and coaching to help the client to understand about everything that you have done and how you have done it. The goal in this stage is to enable the client to learn how to manipulate the database and produce the analysis that you have done. This stage will be longer and relaxed. You work with with one other individual. REQUIREMENTS: - Attention to detail. - Extensive experience in statistical analysis and quantitative modeling. - Ability to concise write reports. - Ability to produce professional-quality tables, charts and other visualizations. - Experience with large relational databases. - Ability to coach and teach some programming elements of your skillset. - Experience analyzing and understanding academic research - Graduate-level academic experience an asset. The type of freelancer that would fit this project is someone who excels in the detailed technical analysis of bigger datasets. This is not a particularly complicated dataset, but requires the ability to manage a large dataset, clean and prepare the data, conduct many standardized statistical tests and conduct recommend analyses appropriate to the data. The initial workload is not complex. The challenge will be in conducting a rigorous, reliable analysis in a relatively compressed timeline. The second stage is simple. You do not need to have a professional presentation of yourself or prepare any educational materials. This work consists of simple, friendly and straight forward conversation. You will be tutoring a friendly, non-threatening individual with a business background. This contract presents the opportunity to establish a healthy work relationship that can lead to considerable future work. Therefore, if you have a solid skillset and looking for an ongoing addition to your work stream, this is an opportunity for you! less

jobtitle: Sports Computer Vision / Video Annotation
content: Hello! Introduction My name is David Velardo. I live in San Francisco and am starting a new company: analytics for pickleball videos. Here is an example of a pickleball video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ImO3uCo3t8I Computer Vision, Labeling Project Overview In the video above, there are three total games played. For each game, there are about 600 “events” (an event is defined as anytime the ball makes contact with something). I require about 4.5 datapoints per event (for example, coordinates of all four players on court, ball height and location, etc). So, for each game, there are about 3000 total datapoints. I am looking to hire an expert (or a firm) to develop the technology to label/extract these datapoints at the lowest cost possible per game while maintaining high accuracy. Camera Notes Assume that the type of camera (different smartphones) and the camera location/angle will never be exactly the same, although, we can explain to players where to setup their camera to get the best results. Exact Data Extraction/Labeling Requirements -Timestamp for each event (an event is defined as any time the ball makes contact with something, usually a players paddle, the ground, or the net -For Ground Events, I simply need the court coordinates where the ball bounced -What’s required for PlayerShot Events: ---Coordinates on court for all four players ---which player is hitting the shot ---if it's a forehand or backhand shot ---the height of ball. jobtitle: Write a query to detect movie release windows (gaps and islands problem)
content: Here is a query and a sample result: https://gist.github.com/gajus/e00e5d966b12f0d0f3a3f38b5e238e6d This query describes the number of movie showtimes in one country on different dates. The task is to determine movie release windows, e.g. Movie Blade Runner (1982) was originally released on 1982, 25th June (1st release window), then it had an extended cut release on 2002, 14th June (2nd release window), etc. We have a data of showtimes (country_id, movie_id, date, event_count). We need to add release_window to every date or NULL for pre-releases/ sparse screenings. Requirements: * A movie release is defined as any range of dates with one or more dates having more than 100 showtimes. * A movie release cut-off is any date with less than 5% of the maximum showtimes within that movie release. * Regardless of the number of count, dates with movie showtimes 30 days after the end of the last release window are ignored. In the sample dataset we see that it describes a single movie release. This movie release peaks on 2019-06-22 (5022 showtimes). We cut-off the showtimes that have less than 5% of the maximum showtimes within this movie release, i.e. we identify rows 3 to 17 (release_window=1), e.g. https://gist.github.com/gajus/49d3ae67ad4b221d38190eded4c000cf#file-result-csv-L3-L17. If there were more showtimes 30 days after this release window with any day having more than 100 showtimes, this would be the 2nd release window. The job is to write an SQL query that creates a materialized view that adds movie release window to every date of the showtime. Attached is a sample dataset for the last 3 months of UK cinema showtimes. less

jobtitle: Find all correlations
content: Find correlations in a data-set with 18 different variables. You can see how the data will be gathered in the attached spreadsheet. It is preferable, if you have some knowledge about SEO. The purpose of this correlations study is to find some correlations that should be used for understanding Amazon's algorithm. An example of a correlation that has been found, could be following: - The 1st organic search result has the keyword mentioned 10 times - Has in average 1k reviews - Has the keyword mentioned 10 times - The keyword is in always in the title of the 1st result - The average price for 1st result product is 20$ - and 1st and 3th quartiles Furthermore, please split up the correlation into general correlations (ex. number of words correlates positive/negative with number of pictures) and into specific based on the best ranking product. Example: #1st ranking product (keyword organic search number, 1) correlates positive/negative with Keyword in title. It may be difficult to know which correlations to look for, if you have no SEO experience or knowledge. If you have knowledge about SEO, you will also know that: "The product that ranks 48th on a given search does not have the keyword in the title" is relevant and "Number of words correlates with the keyword's presence in the review section" is not relevant. Another example of a relevant correlation: The worst ranking product has 1200 words in the description and the keyword mentioned 10 times, whereas the best ranking product only have 400 words and the keyword mentioned 2 times. I think the best results will in relevant cases be found by using smaller parts of the data set to find correlations. Example: Products from the keyword category - "office supplies": The correlation for amount of keywords in title and their ranking is positive/negative. Another thing, which I think we could be able to find: Keywords with 3 words in it has a correlation close to 1.00 with the keyword in the title. This is also something that is exciting to find. You can look at sheet 1 & 2 for inspiration. less

jobtitle: Event Study analysis in R - Stock Price Reaction to M&A announcements
content: I am conducting an event study that looks at the stock price reaction of companies that have acquired a specific type of company. The goal of the analysis would be to estimate the cumulative abnormal return for roughly 1000 cases. To achieve this, one needs to have a market model (regression of past stock returns against benchmark index returns) in order to estimate the "normal returns" for the acquiring companies. The actually achieved returns during the event period are then compared against the "normal returns" to estimate abnormal returns. These abnormal returns should in the next step be scrutinized with a t-test to test for significance. Two options with regards to deliverable: 1. Writing a new R script that estimates the market model, calculating the delta of actual vs. estimated returns, running t-tests to check for significance of findings for approx. 1000 cases. 2. Alternatively, I would very much welcome the use of the EventStudyTools package: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/EventStudy/. less

jobtitle: Analysing laser scan maps using QGIS
content: We’re digitising buildings with laser-scanning equipment and get “point-cloud” files out of it. Sometimes our scanning team misses areas, sometimes the data quality is bad. We want to know which areas we missed and which areas have we captured. I have a video explaining the process in full detail: https://www.dropbox.com/s/k5qvwzto43carz5/QGIS%20How%20to%20extract%20missing%20area%20maps.mov?dl=0 You will need the following tools for the operation: • QGIS with Spatialite and GeoTIFF support • Dropbox and a Dropbox account – we’ll be sharing files through Dropbox. For each building we will make available to you: • 6-band GeoTIFF files in which band 5 contains the captured point count the given floor that we will base our analysis on. • Spatialite databases that have been created from auto-converting CAD files. • A (logarithmic) color ramp configuration to apply as style for the GeoTIFF files. You will execute the following tasks (as explained in training videos) for each building (we will call it a “batch”): 1. You will create a QGIS project file You will execute the following tasks for each floor in the building: 2. You will create a layer group identifying the floor. As floor label you should use the same labels of the GeoTIFF file. The GeoTIFF files are named as follows: {Building-ID}_{Substructure-ID}_{Floor-Level-ID}.tiff 3. You will load the GeoTIFF file and assign the “Arbitrary Transverse Mercator m” projection in meters. You will apply the color ramp as a style as shown in the video. 4. You will load the Spatialite database and assign the “Arbitrary Transverse Mercator mm” projection (in millimeters). You will enable or disable vector layers until you got a good view. 5. You will create a new POLYGON layer in the Spatialite database (in “Arbitrary Transverse Mercator m” projection) called “missing” and mark up all areas missing (white) the the GeoTIFF file. Ignore crossed areas in the Spatialite layers and other areas explained to be excluded in the video. Each area gets a “label” field using the following naming scheme: {Building-ID} {Substruction-ID} L-{Floor-Level-ID} missing {running number} The running number is to be increased for each missing area marked up. The style should be backwards hashed and the label should be clearly visible on the map. 6. You will create a new POLYGON layer in the Spatialite database (in “Arbitrary Transverse Mercator m” projection) called “captured” and mark up the area that have been captured. Please be intelligent about it: You don’t need to create inner rings to markup holes and if the GeoTIFF ends close to Spatialite line vectors, use point snapping. The style should be forward hashed. 7. You will create a new “print layout” (paper format: A4 landscape) that displays the “missing areas” of this floor as shown in the video. Do not include the “captured” layer in the PDF. Each print layout should contain the following label on top of the page: {Building-ID} {Substructure-ID} L-{Floor-ID} You will save the print layout as PDF under the same name as the label above. The purpose of this PDF is: I want to give the map to my scanning team, so they know which areas they have to capture again. The missing area labels must be easily readable, so when I talk to them we can refer to specific areas by their label. Deliverables: • QGIS project file • “captured” and “missing” layers in each floor’s Spatialite database. • PDF file for each floor showing missing areas (like in the video). All deliverables will be shared through Dropbox or in rare cases through upwork file upload. We are hiring multiple freelancers for the job. We will be giving each one of you initially a small sample. The better the quality and the speed of your work, the more work we will assign to you from our backlog. In your application to this job, please specify: • How long have you worked with QGIS software? Do you have any question about what was shown in the video? • Have you worked with point-clouds before? How? What software were you using? Freelancers and agencies who do not answer the questions above in their application will be silently ignored. Please go through the training materials and share with me your questions. If you don’t have any question, I will assign you the first batch as a paid trial run. Please provide me with the following details to set up up for the job: • The email address for your Dropbox account. I will be sharing a folder with you for each registration job that you work on. • Which version of QGIS are you intending to use? Have you checked that it supports Spatialite? less

jobtitle: BigQuery Expert needed for consultation
content: We own a social network web application, that guests, free members and subscribers visit daily to interact with other members of the community, and we would like to be able to track all the events that they generate while doing so. Amongst those events are : following other community members, sending chat messages, giving “likes” to other members etc, all the type of events that you would expect to encounter on a social network (we have a detailed list). We are looking for a BigQuery expert to help us structure the tables and data in order to achieve an optimal setup, both in terms of querying costs & speed, as well as easy scalability and adaptability. The goal is to create a data lake that we can analyse and extract insights and hypothesis from to create new experiments (ab tests) that optimize the product and increase retention as well as conversion. We created a first draft of what the database schema could look like, with nested columns that contain user properties for each event, essentially each record added to the table would contain : - information about the event itself - information about the user that generated it. - timestamp We would like you to take a look and advise us on : - What data to store and what data to ignore ? - How to structure the table for scale and flexibility ? - How to structure the regular querying of the table for optimal cost ? --- Daily aggregation to google sheet ? --- Daily querying from Data Studio ? If you think you can help : please start your application message with "iambigdata" to show that you have read the job description. Here are some queries/questions we would like to use this data for : - How many chat messages did a free member send before subscribing ? --- Same question for members that came from a specific source (user property field) - How many likes does a free member give on average before subscribing ? - How does that average compare to the one of free members that didn’t subscribe ? - How many days on average does it take a free member to subscribe ? --- Same question for members that added their avatar on their sign up date; sign up date+1, .. where is the best correlation with the user subscribing ? - Cohorts of the user lifetime value (and retention) based on having seen a particular page - Cohorts of the user lifetime value based on having uploaded an avatar picture - What succession of events generated the fastest path (and highest rate) to subscription ? - What event is the best predictor of a user subscribing ? what event is the best predictor of a user not subscribing ? We are looking for someone that speaks english and can do the initial consultation during a live video call. less

jobtitle: Data developer needed to do some G Sheet and Data Studio Dashboard work using Supermetrics
content: We run a marketing analytics agency in Calgary (CMO4Hire.com) that makes extensive use of G Suite and Google Data Studio to help our clients (through our software www.dbmms.io). We have a number of client dashboards that are updated either directly from the data source (Analytics, Ads) and we set most of that up. Many of our dashboards are more complex than that. These require us to get data into a G Sheet and then flows into a Data Studio Template. We use Supermetrics as the connector in G Sheets, where we bring in daily data from a number of sources, do some processing in G Sheets, and then offer it to our clients usually through Data Studio Templates. We have an immediate need to find an application data developer who is familiar with G Sheets, App Script, and Supermetrics (although that's pretty easy to learn). We'd also like to find someone who has Biq Query experience, and can eventually help us connect our G Sheets applications to Big Query tables, off loading some processing time (and big data). So, initially your work will be about fixing those problems as they arise. You will also start helping all our clients (and new clients) getting set up on our dashboard system, and eventually deeper programming in Big Query once you understand how we approach things. This is part-time, piecemeal work that we will assign to you, for which you'll be paid hourly. We are looking for a flexible individual (NOT AN AGENCY!) for a long-term relationship where you are one of the people who are on a team serving clients. All work you do must be done with Upwork, recording your screen as you work. You will be paid through Upwork as well. Some communication may occur out of the platform (such as email). Thanks in advance for your time! ~Stephen less

jobtitle: Technical Research: What words in source-code show that a company uses salesforce?
content: The ideal deliverable is a detailed report (or csv) of words, patterns (typically found in HTML code) that would indicate any particular company is using salesforce. Some examples I've found so far are: - if their sourecode refers to pardot they're probably using Salesforce - if their source refers to sfdc or 'salesforce' they're definitely using salesforce - if their source code refers to web-to-lead they are using salesforce - if their careers site refers to salesforce they're probably using salesforce - if they have have a dedicated employee salesforce login site So those are a handful of things I've discovered so far but I think there are probably 100 (or at least a bunch) more tricks that could be used. Once I can make a comprehensive list of these tricks, I can then hire a data-scraping expert to incorporate all of these into a tool to help determine which sites are or are not likely to be running salesforce. Your job is just to help with the 'tricks' and keywords though (some of these keywords may be 'salesforce plug-ins or third-party tools that rely on salesforce btw!). less

jobtitle: Modelling Distributions
content: Hypothetically as a part of our philanthropy efforts we are looking to distribute funds E.g. $1,000,000 total funding amount. We want to give away these funds during discrete periods, where we provide a fixed amount per person per period, until all the funds are exhausted Period 1: Person A -> Receives X Amount Period 2: Person A -> Receives Y Amount Person B -> Receives Y Amount Period 3: Person A -> Receives Y Amount Person B -> Receives Y Amount Person C -> Receives Y Amount Note the number of people asking for a donation each period can vary and the same person can keep coming back for each period asking for a donation. These are the constraints of the Model: How long will the funds last as the number of people seeking donations per period increase. Model different growth rates of people seek donations to see when funds are exhausted. Determine efficient $ distribution each period such that no one person can gain > 2.5% of the total funding amount Provide relationship between funds distributed per person each period vs number of people seeking donations vs periods till funds are exhausted Required: Provide a model which adheres the contraints above. The model must include raw analysis , graphs and justification, with explicit instructions to reproduce the results in the program of your choice: r, python, excel. less

We are looking for some help in testing / developing algorithms to clean up the raw data into usable data for machine learning and to identify whether the test substance is "good" or "bad". Good candidates should be well versed in algorithms involving the removal of fluorescence background from a Raman signal, PCA, typical Raman classification algorithms (root mean square and alike). jobtitle: Investment simulator and back test
content: We want someone to build a simulator that buys and sells equities based on pre-set rules, and back tests against market history to calculate returns. Markets: * UK, Germany, Netherlands, Finland, Sweden, Italy Each day buy according to the following rules: * Dividend yield between 7% and 12% * Market cap greater than EUR 300m and lower than EUR 1 billion * For each company ensure that dividend payments are sustainable: * For last twelve months, the ratio of dividend paid / (free cash flow + one-off costs) < 0.8 Do not buy if: * Revenue has fallen by more than 15% over 2 years * Ratio of revenue/EBITDA has risen by more than 15% over 2 years For each day sell according to the following rules: * Dividend yield is lower than 6% * Dividend yield has fallen by more than 25% since purchase * Dividend yield has risen by more than 15% since purchase We would like for the strategy to be tested against a reasonable time period, at least 5 years (ideally as long as you can do it). If any of these countries is particularly hard to get data for, please tell us and we will consider removing it. We are happy for you to use any tools you’d like to write this software. Ideally python and that we can host. less

jobtitle: Data Analytics
content: Title: Contract Content Analyst - a distant job Description: A contract analyst works with incentive agreement documents. These are legal business documents describing the incentive model established between an airline (or a group of affiliated airlines) and a travel agency. The analyst is required to: 1. Correctly identify the key elements in each incentive plan. For example: start and end date, incentive target types (e.g. coupons sold, revenue in specific currency), incentive payment types (e.g. percentage of qualifying revenue, $ per coupon, fixed incentive), specific terms and conditions related to inclusion for target and for payment (e.g. specific geographies and fare classes included/excluded, specific flight codes or operating airlines), linkage between plans (e.g. one plan is a safety plan, operating only in case the agency failed to meet the minimal target in some other plan) 2. Identify and interact with the customer, in English, to obtain any missing information, such as last year's sales in case of a year-over-year growth target. 3. Correctly model the plan's parameters in a computer-readable file in JSON format. Upload the JSON file to a staging system, and ensure it's correctly displayed in the product. 4. Correctly report to the engineering team any plan characteristics which could not be correctly modeled due to shortcomings of the existing JSON format. Work with the team to suggest extension to the JSON format. Required Experience: Law student with a technical background OR a technology student / junior with aviation or legal background OR travel agent with a mind for technology Company: A startup company from San Francisco, Tel Aviv, and Kiev. Its mission is to make airline-agencies commercial relationships stronger and more effective. That, by our practice, creates a better profit for both sides. Product: a data-driven platform allowing travel agencies and airlines to track incentive plans, in real time, to optimize sales and profit margins. less

content: I am looking for an experienced Python/R user who help me to implement CHAID decision model on my data. The successful applicant will have: * Strong understanding of Python / R * Good knowledge of decision decision tree model mostly CHAID statistic model *Good English and communications skills We use SPSS to generate a CHAID tree. The aim here to run CHAID model on continuous predictors. CHAID decision tree model basically select the predictor that is most significant and then split it into nodes based on significant level. Accordingly it will take predictor and test each one against the predictor variable. We can use Python CHAID package, however we might also need to evaluate other available decision trees package if python CHAID package will not give a valid result. (The SPSS output will be provided for comparison if needed). Data has 5 continuous target variables -- dependent variable and I would like to run CHAID decision tree for each separately to find most significant predictor variables. The data will be in csv format in very tidy form (no data cleaning is needed). less

jobtitle: Need a scoring algorithm to rank products
content: Looking for someone with a math and data science background to create a scoring algorithm to assign a score out of 100 to products. There are about 10 different dimensions on which the product score would be based, and for each of these dimensions there are a few possible options. So what we'd like to do is assign a point value or weight to each option, and then create a scoring formula that will combine them all and output a score out of 100. For example: Product Feature A: -Good = 1 point -Better = 2 points -Best 2.5 points Product Feature B -Good = 0 points -Better = 1 point -Best = 3 points etc. We will provide a detailed list of the different dimensions and details on how we'd like to value them. Also note that the scores should be bell-curved to be mostly distributed in the 65 to 95 range. So the formula needs to ensure that scores never exceed 99, and generally should not be below 50-60. Please include any similar projects you've worked on that you think would be relevant, what your general approach would be, and any questions you have! less

jobtitle: Programmer needed to create a script using an open source software for in-depth data analysis
content: Objective: To determine if the order in which applications are made, and the time between signup and applications, influences conversion rate and transaction value. We are also interested in where applications to certain lenders fall in a sequence, and whether that application was made in isolation, or as part of a cluster of applications. Background: Our service connects users with various lending options based on their profile. The average number of applications per user is approximately 1.6, which has a skewed distribution to a long tail that can stretch to 10 or more applications. A user will sometimes apply to several options in 1 single sessions, and sometimes can wait several months before applying again. We are trying to gain insights from the order and time differences in which the applications are made to ascertain if certain lending options should be presented at different times, or not at all. ‘Success’ for our business is measured in Transactions, ie: the application leads to an approval and there is commission earned. The magnitude of the commission is secondary to whether there is a commission at all. Data Fields: ApplicationID - integer string - unique for each application UserID - integer string - unique for each user StatusID - numerical code for status of the application, which is one of 6 possible codes. User Created Date - Date and time stamp - when the user joined the platform Application Created Date - Date and time stamp - when the application was created Year, Month, Day, Weekday, Week# - simple breakdown of Application Created Date into components LenderID - integer string - unique numerical identifier for each lender PartnerID - integer string - unique numerical identifier for each affiliate partner Credit Score ID - numerical indicator (from 1 to 5) denoting the user’s credit score band (eg: Fair, Good, Excellent etc.) Transaction Value - currency string - value of the commission arising from an application, if any. Transaction Date - when the transaction occurred App. Rec. - if the application was created during the month-end reconciliation process. Any row where this value = 1 has a Transaction Date that is earlier than the Application Date, and thus any analysis comparing those 2 fields should exclude these rows. less

content: Scenario: We produce a bulk amount of product each day, ranging from 20,000 to 100,000 units. Each unit is scored for quality. (Product score) This score ranges from 0.01 to 30. We then separate and package these products into the 5 different sorts (or grades) Each sort has a different market value. Sort 5 is the most valuable and Sort 1 the least valuable Some products are eligible to be placed in any of the 5 categories. Obviously, we would like the to separate the products so that the overall mix of sorts is the most valuable. However, as a population, each sort must satisfy two requirements. The Average Product Score for that product must meet a minimum criteria and the 5%ile score for that product must meet a minimum criteria. If you move a product from one category to another, it changes the average and 5%ile property for both categories. We know the distribution of the Product scores before we undertake the sorting process. (Think of it like a bucket of marbles and we know the Product score of each of the marbles before we sort them) We are looking for a programmer to write code that calculates the optimum sorting set-points for each of the sorts that maximizes the value whilst meeting the minimum value Average Product Score for each sort and the minimum value 5%ile Product Score for each sort. A functional specification is attached. A run time limit for running the code is not specified, as we would like to discuss the trade off between optimisation time and run time. Budget amount is set as minimum. Happy to discuss costs. less

jobtitle: Mobile App Analytics project and implementation
content: We need help to develop our mobile app analytics strategy (for both iOS and Android), evaluate and propose tools for execution of our strategy. Among many other metrics to track, please see some examples below: * Number of app downloads * Number of new account applications / approvals / rejections * Average onboarding time * DAU and MAU * Number customers using certain app functionalities * Demographic characteristics of the audience * Number of contacts in the app * …. we have identified around 50 metrics to track, in addition of filters to these (1/7/30 days, iOS vs Android, Source/Medium, geographical location. Gender, age group). It is likely we can found/develop more. Moreover we want this project to be under right tool/platform to execute our strategy. We’re open-minded on this: Mixpanel, Firebase, Appsee, Amplitude, GA… any tool is good as long as it is the right one for our needs, it has a sensible implementation and a logical price. There is an opportunity to stay engaged with the company on a long term basis. You will be asked to answer the following questions when submitting a proposal: 1. Describe your education and experience with similar projects? 2. Based on the example metrics mentioned, which platform do you think we should consider? 3. What other metrics or use cases do you think we should consider? Please feel free to reach if you have any question beforehand. less
